Filmed at Hong Kong, China and Tobago, Trinidad and Tobago

Jane Hoyt comes to Hong Kong at the height of the Cold War with only one hope, an expatriate American adventurer, pirate, smuggler, and businessman, Hank Lee. Inspector Merryweather of the Hong Kong police tries to warn her off, but she's determined. Her husband, photo journalist Louis Hoyt, is being held by the Red Chinese on espionage charges, and neither the Americans or the British have any intention of rocking the boat to get him out. Her only hope is someone like Hank Lee.
